==English==

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|denounc|e}}

# {{transitive}} to [[criticize]] or [[speak out]] against (someone or something)
# {{transitive}} to openly [[accuse]] (someone) 
# {{transitive}} to formally [[accuse]] (someone)
# {{transitive}} to [[give away]] information about (someone)
# {{transitive}} to [[announce]] the [[termination]] of; especially a [[treaty]]

===Synonyms===
* (''criticize or speak out against''): [[criticize]], [[speak out]]
* (''openly accuse''): [[accuse]], [[blame]]
* (''formally accuse''): [[accuse]], [[charge]], [[report]]
* (''give away information about''): [[give away]], [[snitch]], [[tell]]
* (''announce the termination of; especially a treaty''): [[withdraw from]]

